records.addlTxt:
Defendant James Kenyatta Hogans in court.  Attorney Matthew V Plummer in court for James Kenyatta Hogans.  Prosecuting attorney Josh Milder in court for the State of Wisconsin. Deputy Court Clerk: SD. 
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the victim heard.  Due the lateness of the hour, Court will adjourn sentencing hearing.  Case adjourned, Br. 41.

Defendant James Kenyatta Hogans in court.  Attorney Matthew V Plummer in court for James Kenyatta Hogans.  Prosecuting attorney Josh Milder in court for the State of Wisconsin. Deputy Court Clerk: SD. 
Defendant prepared to enter change of plea.  Hearing proceeded.  Negotiations set forth by the state.

AS TO COUNTS 2 AND 3: Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank. 

AS TO COUNT 1: Pursuant to plea negotiations and on State's motion, Court orders charge dismissed but read-in for sentencing purposes.
Sentencing hearing scheduled for November 14, 2022 at 02:00 pm.
Justice Point Pretrial Services Report received and filed.

Defendant James Kenyatta Hogans appeared by phone.  Attorney Matthew V Plummer appeared by video for James Kenyatta Hogans.  Prosecuting attorney Julie D Knyszek appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin. Deputy Court Clerk: SD. 
Status Conference held.  Defense counsel requests plea and sentencing hearing date.  Case adjourned, Br. 41.
Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for October 28, 2022 at 11:00 am.
Justice Point Pretrial Services Report received and filed.

Attorney Matthew V Plummer in court.  Joshua Milder appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Case in court for pretrial conference. Court is in trial on another case and is unable to proceed on this matter. Case adjourned to Branch 35.  Parties are advised that effective August 1, 2022 this case will be assigned to Judge Audrey Skwierawski, Branch 41 in Room 501 of the Courthouse.  Status conference scheduled for August 23, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Court ordered no contact with RT, JT, and any minor children that live with RT as they were witnesses to the crime and have been witnesses to
other DV incidents between the parties. 
No Contact/No Weapons Order, signed and filed.
Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 3.  Court ordered Defendant to maintain ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY.  No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant James Kenyatta Hogans in court with attorney Theodore OReilly.  Defendant James Kenyatta Hogans in custody.  Nate K. McClure appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  James Kenyatta Hogans appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Rosa, Branch 35. Parties are advised that effective August 1, 2022 this case will be assigned to Judge Audrey Skwierawski, Branch 41 in Room 501 of the Courthouse. Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant pled not guilty.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND QUALIFIES FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.   
This hearing may be streamed live at the discretion of the Court on https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/d9e3cc7f-7791-ec2d-80d3-5bfcdc106eb3  Pre-trial conference scheduled for July 20, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
